---
import Page from '../layouts/Page.astro';
---

<Page title="about -- alexander campos" description="building things to protect how we think.">
  <article>
    <h1>About</h1>

    <p>
      I'm Alex. I build local-first intelligence infrastructure —
      systems that keep your data, your cognition, and your agency
      on your machine.
    </p>

    <p>
      The throughline across everything I work on: language reshapes
      how someone sees themselves — whether it comes from a person
      or a model, the effect is structural. That observation drives
      the tools I build and the questions I chase.
    </p>

    <p>
      That plays out as open-source infrastructure
      (<a href="/projects/forgeframe">ForgeFrame</a>),
      commercial products
      (<a href="https://reframed.works">Reframed</a>, live),
      and independent research
      (<a href="https://guardian-labs.org">Guardian Labs</a>).
    </p>

    <p>
      During the day I work in regulated finance at Capital One —
      process systems, failure analysis, operational infrastructure.
      The rest of the time: this.
    </p>

    <p>
      26. First-gen Guatemalan American. Virginia.
      Self-taught engineer. No CS degree.
      This site is homecooked — Astro, vanilla JS, WebGL shaders, no frameworks.
      If you opened the console, you already know the voice.
    </p>

    <h2>Elsewhere</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/notaprompt">GitHub</a> — open source work</li>
      <li><a href="https://guardian-labs.org">Guardian Labs</a> — independent research</li>
      <li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/alexander-d-campos/">LinkedIn</a> — professional history</li>
      <li><a href="https://substack.com/@alexinthefield">Substack</a> — writing</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      <a href="mailto:alex@campos.works">alex@campos.works</a>
    </p>

    <hr />
    <p style="font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--white-45); text-align: center; margin-top: 2rem;">
      If you made it this far — <a href="/guestbook" style="color: var(--gold-accent); border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--gold-accent);">sign the guestbook</a>.
    </p>
  </article>

